<br>
Basically make a 3 or 4 rods, toss them on the ground, and have one in a general slot.    And click them through a fight (like soloing Slixin Klex in the low 50s) to give you enough mana to maintain an extended pet chaining session.<br>
<br>
I guess I'll hand out single rods to my healers for whatever they want them for, when I hit 56th, so they can use em every 5 min, or only when lom, I don't care.   As for myself, I'll probably click it every 5 minutes for regen purposes and keep Phantom Armor up at all times.<br>
<br>
This nerf sucks.   Raz says something to the effect of &quot;better to have modrods once than never to have them at all.&quot;   Well, I beg to differ, I never even got to enjoy them and I am only one bubble of exp from 56th, with the spell in a bag, ready to be memmed at first DING.<br>
